addToFront(T) - Method in class Custom_CollectionsED.list.arrayLists.ArrayUnorderedList
The addToFront method: takes in an element to be added, as a parameter checks if the array has reached maximum capacity, if so, resizes the array with a call to resizeArray(), which is present in the superclass shifts all of the elements, so that the new element can be added at the front, as the first slot is now empty Finally, the modCount and the counter to keep track of the number of elements are updated.
